# Sentence Building Thinking

Common misconceptions:

children may believe:

```text id="p5r9qe"
long sentence
=
better sentence
```

or:

```text id="u2e6qe"
sentence
=
any group
of words
```

Some may:

```text id="c7r1qe"
write fragments
```

without:

```text id="k3e8qe"
complete thought
```

Example:

students may write:

```text id="n6r4qe"
Running in the park.
```

and think:

```text id="t1e5qe"
complete sentence
```

instead of noticing:

```text id="q7r3qe"
missing subject
or complete idea
```

This skill teaches:

```text id="v9r8qe"
complete-thought reasoning
```

For Grade 3:

focus includes:

Sentence Types:

* statement
* question
* command
* exclamation

Sentence Structure:

* subject
* predicate
* complete sentence
* punctuation

